        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: preserve plugin LLM command auth",
        "body": "## What\n\nPreserves host-bound agent auth profile and model resolution for plugin LLM command/runtime calls and context-engine compactions, including text, Telegram, and Discord native command paths.\n\n## Why\n\nPlugin commands and compactions can run inside an existing session whose selected model/auth profile differs from the default. Without carrying the trusted session binding into the LLM runtime, these paths can fall back to the wrong auth profile or fail to bind an active agent.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Bind context-engine compaction auth\n- Add plugin command LLM runtime\n- Propagate Telegram command auth\n- Propagate Discord command auth\n- Keep auth selection host-owned\n- Preserve static model resolution\n- Cover legacy main sessions\n- Add changelog entry\n\n## Testing\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/runtime/runtime-llm.runtime.test.ts src/plugins/commands.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-plugin.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-memory.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-native-commands.session-meta.test.ts extensions/discord/src/monitor/native-command.plugin-dispatch.test.ts`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `AUTOREVIEW_AUTO_TESTS=0 .agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base upstream/main`\n\nBehavior addressed: plugin and context-engine LLM completions preserve trusted session agent/auth bindings instead of using default credentials or request-controlled auth.\nReal environment tested: local macOS OpenClaw worktree based on upstream/main.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: focused Vitest command above, pnpm build, and autoreview against upstream/main.\nEvidence after fix: 6 test files passed, 141 tests passed; build completed; autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\nObserved result after fix: host-bound LLM runtime receives trusted auth profile bindings for context-engine, text plugin commands, Telegram commands, and Discord commands while public request params cannot choose an auth profile.\nWhat was not tested: live Telegram/Discord provider roundtrip on this branch.\n",
